{
  "texts": [
    "As the standardized rating cannot be computed when the standard deviation is 0, users who have only rated one recipe are automatically excluded from the analysis.",
    "To obtain a unique rating S(x) associated with each recipe, we average the standardized ratings across all users: S(x) = y∈Y R y (x) |Y| with Y the set of all users in RELEXset.",
    "In the remaining part of the paper, we use \"stars\" to refer to the averaged user-standardized ratings.",
    "Fine-Tuning on Recipes.",
    "Given that the recipes consist of text, we follow the recent advances in NLP (Devlin et al., 2019; Liu et al., 2019; Sanh et al., 2019; Brown et al., 2020) and use a pre-trained LLM to predict the quality (starts) of a recipe."
  ]
}